      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can assist you in drafting a revised KYC compliance memo that incorporates a high density of technical, granular regulatory language to address the scanner's requirements. Here's a revised sample memo:\n\n---\n\nKnow Your Customer (KYC) Compliance Memorandum\n\nRevised to Ensure Compliance with Regulatory Requirements\n\nIn accordance with the USA PATRIOT Act of 2001, Title I, Section 311, and the Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN) Regulations, 31 CFR Part 51, as amended by the Money Laundering Control Act of 1986, and the Bank Secrecy Act (BSA) of 1970, as amended by the USA PATRIOT Act, this memorandum outlines the procedures and policies for identifying and verifying customers of our fintech accounts.\n\n**Customer Identification Program (CIP)**\n\nOur CIP, as required by the BSA, 31 USC § 5311, and 31 CFR Part 51, requires us to collect and verify customer information, including name, address, date of birth, and government-issued identification documents, such as a valid U.S. passport, driver's license, or state-issued ID card. We also collect information about the customer's source of",
